---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout title="How to Choose the Perfect Rental Car | Tomobil Car Hire">
  <main class="min-h-screen py-16">
    <article class="container mx-auto px-4 max-w-3xl">
      <header class="mb-8">
        <div class="text-gray-500 mb-2">April 10, 2025</div>
        <h1 class="text-4xl font-bold mb-4">How to Choose the Perfect Rental Car for Your Trip</h1>
      </header>

      <div class="prose prose-lg max-w-none">
        <p>
          Selecting the right rental car can make or break your trip. Whether you're planning a 
          family vacation, business trip, or weekend getaway, this guide will help you choose 
          the perfect vehicle for your needs.
        </p>

        <h2>Consider Your Travel Requirements</h2>
        <h3>Number of Passengers</h3>
        <p>
          First, consider how many people will be traveling:
        </p>
        <ul>
          <li>1-2 people: Compact or economy car</li>
          <li>3-4 people: Midsize sedan</li>
          <li>5+ people: SUV or minivan</li>
        </ul>

        <h3>Luggage Space</h3>
        <p>
          Think about how much cargo space you'll need:
        </p>
        <ul>
          <li>Weekend trip: Compact car might suffice</li>
          <li>Extended vacation: Consider larger trunk space</li>
          <li>Business equipment: SUV or station wagon</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>Type of Journey</h2>
        <p>
          Different trips require different vehicles:
        </p>
        <ul>
          <li>City driving: Compact car for easy parking</li>
          <li>Highway travel: Midsize for comfort</li>
          <li>Mountain areas: SUV with 4-wheel drive</li>
          <li>Luxury travel: Premium or luxury vehicle</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>Budget Considerations</h2>
        <p>
          Remember to factor in:
        </p>
        <ul>
          <li>Daily rental rate</li>
          <li>Fuel efficiency</li>
          <li>Insurance costs</li>
          <li>Additional fees</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>Vehicle Features</h2>
        <p>
          Consider which features are important for your trip:
        </p>
        <ul>
          <li>GPS navigation</li>
          <li>Bluetooth connectivity</li>
          <li>Child car seats</li>
          <li>Automatic vs. manual transmission</li>
          <li>Climate control</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>Making the Final Decision</h2>
        <p>
          To make your final choice:
        </p>
        <ol>
          <li>Compare prices across different car categories</li>
          <li>Read reviews of specific models</li>
          <li>Check for current promotions</li>
          <li>Consider upgrading if the price difference is minimal</li>
        </ol>

        <p>
          Remember, the perfect rental car is one that balances comfort, practicality, and budget. 
          Don't hesitate to ask rental agents for recommendations based on your specific needs.
        </p>
      </div>
    </article>
  </main>
</Layout>
